text: Bazargulovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Uralsky Selsoviet,Uchalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 47 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 39 km from Uchaly, 9 km from Uralsk. == References == Category:Rural localities in Uchalinsky District
title: Bazargulovo
